org.apache.poi.hssf.usermodel

Class HSSFWorkbook

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.poi.POIDocument
      • org.apache.poi.hssf.usermodel.HSSFWorkbook
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Closeable, java.lang.AutoCloseable, java.lang.Iterable<Sheet>, Workbook 

    public final class HSSFWorkbook
extends POIDocument
implements Workbook
    High level representation of a workbook. This is the first object most users will construct whether they are reading or writing a workbook. It is also the top level object for creating new sheets/etc.(工作簿的高级表示。无论是阅读还是编写工作簿，这都是大多数用户都会构建的第一个对象。它也是用于创建新表格/等的顶级对象。)
    See Also:
    InternalWorkbook, HSSFSheet

    • Field Detail

      • INITIAL_CAPACITY

        public static final int INITIAL_CAPACITY
        used for compile-time performance/memory optimization. This determines the initial capacity for the sheet collection. Its currently set to 3. Changing it in this release will decrease performance since you're never allowed to have more or less than three sheets!(用于编译时性能/内存优化。这决定了图纸收集的初始容量。目前设置为3。在此版本中更改它将降低性能，因为您永远不允许拥有多于或少于三张表格！)

      • createSheet

        public HSSFSheet createSheet(java.lang.String sheetname)
        Create a new sheet for this Workbook and return the high level representation. Use this to create new sheets.

        Note that Excel allows sheet names up to 31 chars in length but other applications (such as OpenOffice) allow more. Some versions of Excel crash with names longer than 31 chars, others - truncate such names to 31 character.

        POI's SpreadsheetAPI silently truncates the input argument to 31 characters. Example:

        
     Sheet sheet = workbook.createSheet("My very long sheet name which is longer than 31 chars"); // will be truncated
     assert 31 == sheet.getSheetName().length();
     assert "My very long sheet name which i" == sheet.getSheetName();

        Except the 31-character constraint, Excel applies some other rules:

        Sheet name MUST be unique in the workbook and MUST NOT contain the any of the following characters:

        • 0x0000
        • 0x0003
        • colon (:)
        • backslash (\)
        • asterisk (*)
        • question mark (?)
        • forward slash (/)
        • opening square bracket ([)
        • closing square bracket (])
        The string MUST NOT begin or end with the single quote (') character.

        (为此工作簿创建新工作表并返回高级表示。使用此创建新表格。请注意，Excel允许表格名称长度最多为31个字符，但其他应用程序（例如OpenOffice）允许更多字符。某些版本的Excel因名称超过31个字符而崩溃，其他版本则将此类名称截断为31个字符。DOE的数据表API会悄悄将输入参数截断为31个字符。示例： 工作表表=工作簿.工作表（“我的超长工作表名称超过31个字符”）; //将被截断 assert 31 == sheet.getSheetName（）. size（）; assert“我的非常长的表格名称，其中i”== sheet.getSheetName（）; 除了31个字符的限制外，Excel还应用一些其他规则：工作表名称在工作簿中必须唯一，并且不得包含以下任何字符：0x 0000 0x 003 colore（：）反斜线（\）星号（*）问号（？）正斜杠（/）开头方括号（[）结尾方括号（]）字符串不得以单引号（'）字符串开始或结束。)
        Specified by:

      • removeSheetAt

        public void removeSheetAt(int index)
        Removes sheet at the given index.

        Care must be taken if the removed sheet is the currently active or only selected sheet in the workbook. There are a few situations when Excel must have a selection and/or active sheet. (For example when printing - see Bug 40414).

        This method makes sure that if the removed sheet was active, another sheet will become active in its place. Furthermore, if the removed sheet was the only selected sheet, another sheet will become selected. The newly active/selected sheet will have the same index, or one less if the removed sheet was the last in the workbook.

        (给定索引处的电子表格。如果删除的工作表是工作簿中当前活动的工作表或唯一选定的工作表，则必须小心。在某些情况下，Excel必须具有选择和/或活动工作表。(For打印时的示例-请参阅Bug 40414）。此方法确保如果删除的表格处于活动状态，另一张表格将在其位置变得活动状态。此外，如果删除的纸张是唯一选择的纸张，则将选择另一张纸张。新活动/选择的工作表将具有相同的索引，如果删除的工作表是工作簿中的最后一个，则会少一个。)
        Specified by:

      • setForceFormulaRecalculation

        public void setForceFormulaRecalculation(boolean value)
        Whether the application shall perform a full recalculation when the workbook is opened.

        Typically you want to force formula recalculation when you modify cell formulas or values of a workbook previously created by Excel. When set to true, this flag will tell Excel that it needs to recalculate all formulas in the workbook the next time the file is opened.

        Note, that recalculation updates cached formula results and, thus, modifies the workbook. Depending on the version, Excel may prompt you with "Do you want to save the changes in filename?" on close.

        (当工作簿打开时，应用程序是否应执行完全重新计算。通常，当您修改以前由Excel创建的工作簿的单元公式或值时，您希望强制重新计算公式。当设置为true时，此标志将告诉Excel下次打开文件时需要重新计算工作簿中的所有公式。请注意，重新计算会更新缓存的公式结果，从而修改工作簿。根据版本的不同，Excel可能会提示您“是否要将更改保存为文件名？“在关闭。)
        Specified by:
        setForceFormulaRecalculation in interface Workbook(setForce公式界面工作簿中的重新计算)
        Parameters:
        value - true if the application will perform a full recalculation of workbook values when the workbook is opened(value -如果应用程序将在打开工作簿时执行工作簿值的完全重新计算，则为true)
        Since:
        3.8
